Synthesis and characterization of new materials using solid state reactions and analysis of their crystal structures using X-ray diffraction (XRD).
Study of the effect of different sintering temperatures on the properties of ceramics using XRD, scanning electron microscopy (SEM), and mechanical testing.
Investigation of the magnetic properties of different materials using magnetometry and analysis of the magnetic phase diagrams.
Study of the effect of different doping levels on the electronic properties of semiconductors using Hall effect measurements and analysis of the carrier concentration and mobility.
Synthesis and characterization of new materials with ferroelectric properties and analysis of their ferroelectric behavior using polarization-electric field (P-E) hysteresis loops.
Investigation of the effect of different annealing temperatures on the electrical conductivity of metal oxides using four-point probe measurements and analysis of the activation energy and carrier concentration.
Synthesis and characterization of new materials with luminescent properties and analysis of their photoluminescence behavior using spectroscopy.
Study of the phase transformations of different materials using differential scanning calorimetry (DSC) and analysis of the resulting phase diagrams.
Investigation of the thermal stability and decomposition behavior of different materials using thermogravimetric analysis (TGA) and analysis of the decomposition products.
Synthesis and characterization of new materials with high surface area using solid state reactions and analysis of their surface properties using gas adsorption techniques.
